Subinterfaces of IExpression in org.tair.sql.expression
 interface IAliasedExpression
          An aliased expression is an expression that has a SQL alias (AS clause).
 interface IMultipleParameterExpression
          An interface for SQL expressions that contain multiple bind parameters; these will usually be WHERE clause expressions
 interface IScalarExpression<T>
          A scalar expression results in a value of type T on execution of the SQL statement.
 interface ISelectExpression<T>
          An aliased, scalar expression that appears in a SELECT list of expressions; if nothing is constructed, the expression will be the NULL keyword.
 interface ISingleParameterExpression<P>
          A SQL expression suitable for use in a SELECT list or as a value expression in a WHERE clause, GROUP BY clause, or ORDER BY clause; the expression may include a single parameter or may be just a parameter itself; the expression always evaluates to a single value of type P
 interface ISubqueryExpression
          An interface for a SQL expression that is a subquery of some kind
